A towering crane in NYC toppled, crashing into apartment buildings, killing four and sparking a rescue operation.
The 19-story crane split, pulverizing buildings and causing fatalities.
The collapse, one of the city's worst, occurred during construction, with pieces falling and damaging structures.
Despite inspections, the crane failed, leading to tragic consequences.
The incident highlighted the risks of construction in NYC, where cranes are essential yet pose dangers.
The aftermath involved rescue efforts, removal of debris, and investigations into the cause of the collapse.
Tragedies like this underscore the importance of safety in construction projects.
